.row.servers
  .span8.columns
    %form{:action => "/servers", :method => :post}
      .clearfix
        %label{:for => "server_name"} Name
        .input
          %input{:type => "text", :name => "server[name]", :id => "server_name"}
      .clearfix
        %label{:for => "server_url"} Monit URL
        .input
          %input{:type => "text", :name => "server[url]", :id => "server_url"}
      .clearfix
        .input
          %input.btn{:type => "submit", :value => "Add Server"}
  .span8.columns
    .alert-message.block-message.info
      %h3.title Creating Servers
      %p
        Monit servers can either run on the server they monitor, or on a single monitoring server. You need to enable a couple of settings in your <code>monitrc</code> - notably, the web interface, and access control to allow the IP address of the <strong>MonitMonit</strong> server.

%table{:class => "common-table zebra-striped"}
  %thead
    %tr
      %th Server ID
      %th Server Name
      %th Server URL
      %th
  %tbody
    - @servers.each do |server|
      %tr
        %td= server.id
        %td= server.name || "[Not given]"
        %td= server.url
        %td.delete-wrapper
          %form{:action => "/servers/#{server.id}/delete", :method => :post}
            %button.btn.danger{:type => "submit"} Delete

